                <note rend="inline" type="source">740.0011 European War 1939/13484b: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Acting Secretary of State</gloss> to
                        the Ambassador in the Soviet Union</hi> (<persName type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Steinhardt</hi>
                    </persName>)</head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1941-07-27T16:00:00-04:00"
                            >July 27, 1941—4 p.m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>930. The President has instructed Harry Hopkins,<note n="42" xml:id="d747fn42"
                        >Special Assistant to the President.</note> who is now in London, to proceed
                    by air to Moscow. He will be leaving Monday night<note n="43" xml:id="d747fn43"
                        >July 28.</note> via Archangel. The objective of his mission is primarily to
                        <pb facs="0810" n="798" xml:id="pg_798"/> investigate how best we can
                    furnish material assistance to the Soviet Union at this time. The details of his
                    mission he will himself explain to you upon his arrival.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Welles</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
